About me
My name is Daniel Galvez. I'm a Full Stack Javascript Engineer with more than 12 years of experience working for top web companies. My expertise covers from web performance optimization to robust testing platforms in highly complex and fast pace development environments.

Client side scalibility is my favourite subject and I can help you getting your website to the next level.

Last but not least, I'm a jQuery core contributor, so you can surely count on my bullet proof JavaScript skills.

Frontend Optimization Expert
I was hired by Booking.com in December 2011 to join a team of experts in frontend optimization who would tackle the performance issues the frontend team was facing. Taking into account the A/B testing oriented development workflow of the Booking.com frontend department we implemented a number of tools to directly improve the website rendering times and made sure the right measures were in place to avoid the website's performance degradation due to the nature of such an environment where many developers with different levels of skills were pushing code live every hour. Some examples of the tasks and tools we implemented:
  • Cluster generating customized CSS on the fly for the specific client request.
  • Multi CDN setup experimentation per country.
  • Transparent client side component lazy AJAX loading.
  • DNS server optimizations.
  • HTML postprocessing optimizing rendering times by empowering resource loading parallelization.
